---
import AppShell from "../frontend/thinkinglabs-ui/components/AppShell.astro";
import ThinkinglabsUiPage from "../layouts/ThinkinglabsUiPage.astro";
---

<ThinkinglabsUiPage
  title="Privacy — thinkinglabs"
  description="thinkinglabs does not track visitors. No analytics, no cookies, no fingerprinting."
>
  <AppShell activeNav="Index">
    <section class="tl-page-head is-spacious">
      <h1>Privacy.</h1>
    </section>

    <article class="tl-privacy-prose tl-prose-body">
      <p class="tl-privacy-lede">This site does not track you.</p>

      <p>
        thinkinglabs is static HTML generated from a public markdown repository. There is no
        analytics product sitting behind the pages, no cookie banner because there are no site
        cookies to accept, and no client-side fingerprinting script trying to infer who you are.
      </p>

      <p>
        The site does not write to localStorage, sessionStorage, IndexedDB, or any other browser
        storage API. It does not include pixels, embedded trackers, or third-party SDKs that quietly
        assemble a profile of your reading habits.
      </p>

      <h2>Infrastructure logs</h2>

      <p>
        The hosting layer may keep ordinary operational request logs, such as an IP address, path,
        timestamp, user agent, or status code. Those records are the kind of transient plumbing
        hosts use for abuse mitigation and debugging. They are not read, joined, sold, or used by
        this site to identify readers.
      </p>

      <h2>External places</h2>

      <p>
        Links to other domains leave this site. Once you follow one, your browser is interacting
        with that domain and its own policies apply. The privacy promise here is intentionally
        narrow: while you are reading thinkinglabs pages, the site itself is not trying to observe
        you.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>

      <p>
        Questions about privacy or anything else can go through <a href="/contact/">/contact</a>.
        There are no form handlers on this site; any conversation happens directly through the
        channels listed there.
      </p>
    </article>
  </AppShell>
</ThinkinglabsUiPage>

<style>
  .tl-privacy-prose {
    width: var(--tl-center);
    margin: -4vh auto 18vh;
  }

  .tl-privacy-lede {
    max-width: 15ch;
    color: var(--tl-ink);
    font-size: clamp(34px, 5vw, 64px);
    font-weight: 620;
    line-height: 0.96;
    letter-spacing: -0.05em;
  }

  .tl-privacy-prose h2 {
    margin-top: clamp(3.5rem, 9vh, 5.5rem);
    color: var(--tl-ink);
    font-size: clamp(23px, 3vw, 36px);
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1;
    letter-spacing: -0.035em;
  }

  .tl-privacy-prose a {
    color: inherit;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
    text-underline-offset: 4px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 767px) {
    .tl-privacy-prose {
      width: min(100% - 40px, 43.75rem);
      margin-top: -2vh;
    }
  }
</style>
